iend"},{"character":"Egwene al'Vere","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Meets Moiraine and her Warder Lan, receives a silver penny from Moiraine."},{"name":"Bran al'Vere","aliases":["Mayors of Emond's Field","Bran"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prophecy Fulfilled","currentLocation":"Emond's Field","description":"The mayor of Emond's Field who is usually calm and pragmatic.","relationships":[{"character":"Rand al'Thor","relationship":"knows Rand and his father Tam"},{"character":"Master al'Vere","relationship":"respects Master al'Vere as a skilled blacksmith"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed the upcoming Festival and the arrival of a gleeman and potential fireworks."},{"name":"Cenn Buie","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prophecy Fulfilled","currentLocation":"Emond's Field","description":"A sceptical villager who has little faith in the coming festival activities.","relationships":[{"character":"Bran al'Vere","relationship":"disagrees with the mayor on various issues and feels skeptical"},{"character":"Master al'Vere","relationship":"knows him as a blacksmith"}],"recentEvents":"Expressed skepticism about the arrival of the gleeman and the prospects of fireworks."},{"name":"Egwene al'Vere","aliases":["Egwene"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Village in the Two Rivers","currentLocation":"Emond's Field","description":"A young woman of the Two Rivers, intelligent and curious, considering becoming a Wisdom.","relationships":[{"character":"Rand al'Thor","relationship":"friend and romantic interest"},{"character":"Nynaeve al'Meara","relationship":"mentor"}],"recentEvents":"Egwene discusses with Rand about his talk of the black-cloaked rider and warns him against scaring children. She also expresses her plans to be a Wisdom and her curiosity about the world outside the Two Rivers."},{"name":"Perrin Aybar","aliases":["Perrin"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Village in the Two Rivers","currentLocation":"Emond's Field","description":"A young man of the Two Rivers, strong and practical, with a keen sense of responsibility.","relationships":[{"character":"Rand al'Thor","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Mat Cauthon","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Master Luhhan","relationship":"blacksmith and mentor"}],"recentEvents":"Perrin recounts his sighting of the black-cloaked rider to Rand and Mat. Master Luhhan believes Perrin was perhaps seeing shadows, but Perrin insists on his observation."},{"name":"Mat Cauthon","aliases":["Mat"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Village in the Two Rivers","currentLocation":"Emond's Field","description":"A young man of the Two Rivers known for his quick wit and gambles.","relationships":[{"character":"Rand al'Thor","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Perrin Aybar","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Egwene al'Vere","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Mat retells his encounter with the rider to Rand and Egwene. He expresses belief in Perrin's sighting even in the face of skepticism."},{"name":"Nynaeve al'Meara","aliases":["Nynaeve"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Village in the Two Rivers","currentLocation":"Emond's Field","description":"A young woman from the Two Rivers, determined and practical, teaching Egwene about becoming a Wisdom.","relationships":[{"character":"Egwene al'Vere","relationship":"mentor"},{"character":"Elaine Orde","relationship":"cousin"}],"recentEvents":"Nynaeve enters the inn for a meeting about the mysterious events occurring in their village, as she tries to gather information from the peddler and the Women’s Circle."}],"locations":[{"name":"The Land","description":"A place where the Shadow fell and the world was broken by Lews Therin's destructive act."},{"name":"Island","description":"An island formed by the lava flow from the mountain created by Lews Therin's channeling of the One Power."},{"name":"Emond's Field","description":"A village in the Two Rivers, home to Rand, Perrin, and Mat, with a Green where community events take place, including the Spring Pole for unmarried women."}],"summary":"Rand, Egwene, Perrin, and Mat discuss sightings of a mysterious black-cloaked rider in Emond's Field. The boys are convinced of the rider's existence, while Egwene dismisses it as nothing more than tales to scare children. Nynaeve goes inside the inn to gather information on the recent events from a visiting peddler and the Women’s Circle."}},{"index":41,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Lews Therin Telamon","aliases":["Dragon"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"And it came to pass in those days","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A powerful and proud channeller who led the fight against the Shadow.","relationships":[{"character":"Ilyena Sunhair","relationship":"Wife"},{"character":"The Betrayer","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Lews Therin faces his guilt over his actions that led to the Breaking of the World, his wife's death, and channels the One Power in a destructive act."},{"name":"The Betrayer","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"And it came to pass in those days","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A powerful channeller who aided the Shadow against Lews Therin.","relationships":[{"character":"Lews Therin Telamon","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"The Betrayer confronts Lews Therin about his past actions and the breaking of the world, and warns him that the conflict between them will continue until the end of time."},{"name":"Rand al'Thor","aliases":["Rand","TheDragonReborn"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Village Takes a Council","currentLocation":"Emond's Field","description":"A young farm boy who turns out to have a significant destiny waiting for him.","relationships":[{"character":"Tam al'Thor","relationship":"Guardian and mentor"}],"recentEvents":"Rand becomes convinced his observations about the black-cloaked rider are credible as his father believes him and confirms others have seen the rider too. Rand feels supported by the villagers' collective awareness and belief in the threat."},{"name":"Matrim Cauthon","aliases":["Mat"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 8: The Peddler","currentLocation":"Emond's Field, Two Rivers","description":"Known for his gambling and joking; may possess a mysterious pendant.","relationships":[{"character":"Rand al'Thor","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Perrin Aybara","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Egwene al'Vere","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Meets Moiraine and her Warder Lan, receives a silver penny from Moiraine."},{"name":"Bran al'Vere","aliases":["Mayors of Emond's Field","Bran"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prophecy Fulfilled","currentLocation":"Emond's Field","description":"The mayor of Emond's Field who is usually calm and pragmatic.","relationships":[{"character":"Rand al'Thor","relationship":"knows Rand and his father Tam"},{"character":"Master al'Vere","relationship":"respects Master al'Vere as a skilled blacksmith"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed the upcoming Festival and the arrival of a gleeman and potential fireworks."},{"name":"Cenn Buie","aliases":["Cenn"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Village Takes a Council","currentLocation":"Emond's Field","description":"A skeptical and sometimes contentious member of the Village Council.","relationships":[{"character":"Bran al'Thor","relationship":"Council member and occasional antagonist"},{"character":"Tam al'Thor","relationship":"Council colleague, somewhat suspicious of Tam"}],"recentEvents":"Cenn’s skepticism contrasts with the rest of the Council’s decision-making process, highlighting the division in the community over the threat of outsiders and the war."},{"name":"Egwene al'Vere","aliases":["Egwene"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Village in the Two Rivers","currentLocation":"Emond's Field","description":"A young woman of the Two Rivers, intelligent and curious, considering becoming a Wisdom.","relationships":[{"character":"Rand al'Thor","relationship":"friend and romantic interest"},{"character":"Nynaeve al'Meara","relationship":"mentor"}],"recentEvents":"Egwene discusses with Rand about his talk of the black-cloaked rider and warns him against scaring children. She also expresses her plans to be a Wisdom and her curiosity about the world outside the Two Rivers."},{"name":"Perrin Aybar","aliases":["Perrin"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Village in the Two Rivers","currentLocation":"Emond's Field","description":"A young man of the Two Rivers, strong and practical, with a keen sense of responsibility.","relationships":[{"character":"Rand al'Thor","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Mat Cauthon","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Master Luhhan","relationship":"blacksmith and mentor"}],"recentEvents":"Perrin recounts his sighting of the black-cloaked rider to Rand and Mat. Master Luhhan believes Perrin was perhaps seeing shadows, but Perrin insists on his observation."},{"name":"Mat Cauthon","aliases":["Mat"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Village in the Two Rivers","currentLocation":"Emond's Field","description":"A young man of the Two Rivers known for his quick wit and gambles.","relationships":[{"character":"Rand al'Thor","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Perrin Aybar","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Egwene al'Vere","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Mat retells his encounter with the rider to Rand and Egwene. He expresses belief in Perrin's sighting even in the face of skepticism."},{"name":"Nynaeve al'Meara","aliases":["Nynaeve"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Village in the Two Rivers","currentLocation":"Emond's Field","description":"A young woman from the Two Rivers, determined and practical, teaching Egwene about becoming a Wisdom.","relationships":[{"character":"Egwene al'Vere","relationship":"mentor"},{"character":"Elaine Orde","relationship":"cousin"}],"recentEvents":"Nynaeve enters the inn for a meeting about the mysterious events occurring in their village, as she tries to gather information from the peddler and the Women’s Circle."},{"name":"Tam al'Thor","aliases":["Tam","Rand's Guardian"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Village Takes a Council","currentLocation":"Emond's Field","description":"A strong influence in Rand's life, often seen as a father figure despite them not being closely related.","relationships":[{"character":"Rand al'Thor","relationship":"Guardian and mentor"}],"recentEvents":"Tam believes Rand’s observations about the black-cloaked rider, helping to validate his concerns and reinforcing the community's vigilance. Tam and Rand are returning home while ensuring Rand monitors the situation."},{"name":"Padan Fain","aliases":["Fain","The Traveler"],"importance":"antagonist","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Village Takes a Council","currentLocation":"Emond's Field","description":"A traveler and former businessman who is revealed to have sinister intentions and a connection to the forces of shadow.","relationships":[{"character":"Rand al'Thor","relationship":"Target of suspicion and a possible threat"}],"recentEvents":"Fain evades the village’s notice during the questioning by the Council, though villagers like Rand observe him moving about. The nature of his presence and activities remain unclear but increasingly suspicious."},{"name":"Bran al'Thor","aliases":["Bran","The Mayor of Emond's Field"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Village Takes a Council","currentLocation":"Emond's Field","description":"The mayor of Emond’s Field, a capable and prudent leader during times of crisis.","relationships":[{"character":"Rand al'Thor","relationship":"Mayor of Rand's home village"},{"character":"Tam al'Thor","relationship":"Friend and colleague in village leadership"}],"recentEvents":"Bran is leading the Council's decision-making process amidst concerns about Padan Fain and the war in Ghealdan, aiming to reassure the villagers about their safety."},{"name":"Haral Luhhan","aliases":["Master Smith","Luhhan"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Village Takes a Council","currentLocation":"Emond's Field","description":"The town blacksmith, known for his practical and cautious approach to issues.","relationships":[{"character":"Rand al'Thor","relationship":"Friend and mentor in village concerns"}],"recentEvents":"Haral mentions Perrin’s observations about jumping shadows, reinforcing the credibility of the sightings of the strange rider and contributing to the Council’s understanding of the situation."},{"name":"Jon Thane","aliases":["Jon"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Village Takes a Council","currentLocation":"Emond's Field","description":"Father of a son who has reported a strange sighting around the village.","relationships":[{"character":"Rand al'Thor","relationship":"Contemporaries within the village community"}],"recentEvents":"Jon's son has sighted the black-cloaked rider, providing evidence to the Council alongside other children’s accounts."},{"name":"Samel Crawe","aliases":["Samel"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Village Takes a Council","currentLocation":"Emond's Field","description":"Father of Bandry, a son who witnessed the mysterious traveler.","relationships":[{"character":"Rand al'Thor","relationship":"Neighbor and fellow villager"}],"recentEvents":"Samel’s son, Bandry, has also reported sightings of the suspicious figure, supporting the growing concern among the villagers."}],"locations":[{"name":"The Land","description":"A place where the Shadow fell and the world was broken by Lews Therin's destructive act."},{"name":"Island","description":"An island formed by the lava flow from the mountain created by Lews Therin's channeling of the One Power."},{"name":"Emond's Field","description":"A village on the edge of the Two Rivers, characterized by its agricultural lifestyle and tight-knit community."},{"name":"The Village Council","description":"An assembly of respected members within the community who meet to discuss and decide on matters concerning Emond's Field."}],"summary":"The village of Emond's Field addresses the looming threats of the war in Ghealdan and the mysterious presence of a suspicious traveler, Padan Fain, through the guidance of its council. Despite initial skepticism, the collective observations of young villagers, including Rand, confirm the necessity for vigilance. The villagers grapple with the balance between maintaining their pastoral life and preparing for potential dangers."}},{"index":42,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Lews Therin Telamon","aliases":["Dragon"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"And it came to pass in those days","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A powerful and proud channeller who led the fight against the Shadow.","relationships":[{"character":"Ilyena Sunhair","relationship":"Wife"},{"character":"The Betrayer","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Lews Therin faces his guilt over his actions that led to the Breaking of the World, his wife's death, and channels the One Power in a destructive act."},{"name":"The Betrayer","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"And it came to pass in those days","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A powerful channeller who aided the Shadow against Lews Therin.","relationships":[{"character":"Lews Therin Telamon","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"The Betrayer confronts Lews Therin about his past actions and the breaking of the world, and warns him that the conflict between them will continue until the end of time."},{"name":"Rand al'Thor","aliases":["Rand","Lews Therin"],"importance":"main","status