"relationship":"Target of suspicion and a possible threat"}],"recentEvents":"Fain evades the village’s notice during the questioning by the Council, though villagers like Rand observe him moving about. The nature of his presence and activities remain unclear but increasingly suspicious."},{"name":"Bran al'Thor","aliases":["Bran","The Mayor of Emond's Field"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Village Takes a Council","currentLocation":"Emond's Field","description":"The mayor of Emond’s Field, a capable and prudent leader during times of crisis.","relationships":[{"character":"Rand al'Thor","relationship":"Mayor of Rand's home village"},{"character":"Tam al'Thor","relationship":"Friend and colleague in village leadership"}],"recentEvents":"Bran is leading the Council's decision-making process amidst concerns about Padan Fain and the war in Ghealdan, aiming to reassure the villagers about their safety."},{"name":"Haral Luhhan","aliases":["Master Smith","Luhhan"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Village Takes a Council","currentLocation":"Emond's Field","description":"The town blacksmith, known for his practical and cautious approach to issues.","relationships":[{"character":"Rand al'Thor","relationship":"Friend and mentor in village concerns"}],"recentEvents":"Haral mentions Perrin’s observations about jumping shadows, reinforcing the credibility of the sightings of the strange rider and contributing to the Council’s understanding of the situation."},{"name":"Jon Thane","aliases":["Jon"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Village Takes a Council","currentLocation":"Emond's Field","description":"Father of a son who has reported a strange sighting around the village.","relationships":[{"character":"Rand al'Thor","relationship":"Contemporaries within the village community"}],"recentEvents":"Jon's son has sighted the black-cloaked rider, providing evidence to the Council alongside other children’s accounts."},{"name":"Samel Crawe","aliases":["Samel"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Village Takes a Council","currentLocation":"Emond's Field","description":"Father of Bandry, a son who witnessed the mysterious traveler.","relationships":[{"character":"Rand al'Thor","relationship":"Neighbor and fellow villager"}],"recentEvents":"Samel’s son, Bandry, has also reported sightings of the suspicious figure, supporting the growing concern among the villagers."},{"name":"Kari al'Thor","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"The Arrival","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Rand's mother, who died before Rand's memories.","relationships":[{"character":"Rand al'Thor","relationship":"Son"},{"character":"Tam al'Thor","relationship":"Husband"}],"recentEvents":"Tam mentions Kari in his fever dreams, causing distress to Rand."},{"name":"Unnamed rider (black-cloaked)","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"The Return","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A mysterious figure in black who seems to be watching Rand and Tam quietly from his horse.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"The black-cloaked rider silently observes Rand and Tam as they travel through the forest, showing animosity towards them."},{"name":"Moiraine Damodred","aliases":["The Traveler","Aes Sedai"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 2: The Wolf Gives Warning","currentLocation":"Emond's Field","description":"A mysterious woman who is an Aes Sedai, seeking the young ones who may be ta'veren.","relationships":[{"character":"Rand al'Thor","relationship":"Guiding him in her quest"},{"character":"Lan Mandragoran","relationship":"Warder"}],"recentEvents":"Conducted an investigation on the dead Trollocs found after the attack. Agreed to help Rand's father based on Rand's request."},{"name":"Lan Mandragoran","aliases":["The Lion of Malk Malkiel","A Guardian"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Village of Emond's Field","currentLocation":"Emond's Field","description":"A Warder of Moiraine Sedai, pledged to protect her and Rand al'Thor.","relationships":[{"character":"Moiraine Sedai","relationship":"Warder"},{"character":"Rand al'Thor","relationship":"Guardian"}],"recentEvents":"Acts alongside Moiraine to protect Rand and investigate unusual events in Emond's Field."},{"name":"Wisdom of Emond's Field","aliases":["Tarenne"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 2: The Wolf Gives Warning","currentLocation":"Emond's Field","description":"She is the village healer and advisor, known for her knowledge and practical approach to village matters.","relationships":[{"character":"Rand al'Thor","relationship":"Village healer who treated his father's wound"}],"recentEvents":"Declared herself unable to cure Rand's father's fever as it is beyond her abilities."},{"name":"Mistress al'Vere","aliases":["Egwene","Adoptive Mother"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Village of Emond's Field","currentLocation":"Home of Mistress al'Vere","description":"Adoptive mother to Rand, the healer of Emond's Field.","relationships":[{"character":"Rand al'Thor","relationship":"Adoptive Son"},{"character":"Mayor of Emond's Field","relationship":"Spouse"}],"recentEvents":"Cares for the sick Rand and his unconscious father, Tam. Interacts with Moiraine Sedai regarding Rand and Tam."},{"name":"Mayor of Emond's Field","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Village of Emond's Field","currentLocation":"Home of Mistress al'Vere","description":"The mayor of Emond's Field, concerned about village happenings.","relationships":[{"character":"Rand al'Thor","relationship":"Villager"},{"character":"Mistress al'Vere","relationship":"Spouse"}],"recentEvents":"Provides Rand with instructions about resting and discusses the village's recent events with Rand."},{"name":"Moiraine Sedai","aliases":["Moiraine","Aes Sedai"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Village of Emond's Field","currentLocation":"Emond's Field","description":"A wise and skilled Aes Sedai who travels incognito and is pivotal to Rand's destiny.","relationships":[{"character":"Rand al'Thor","relationship":"Teacher and Guide"},{"character":"Lan Mandragoran","relationship":"Guardian"}],"recentEvents":"Ensures the safety of Rand and Tam by warning Rand of potential threats and providing guidance."}],"locations":[{"name":"The Land","description":"A place where the Shadow fell and the world was broken by Lews Therin's destructive act."},{"name":"Island","description":"An island formed by the lava flow from the mountain created by Lews Therin's channeling of the One Power."},{"name":"Emond's Field","description":"A village on the edge of the Two Rivers, characterized by its agricultural lifestyle and tight-knit community."},{"name":"The Village Council","description":"An assembly of respected members within the community who meet to discuss and decide on matters concerning Emond's Field."},{"name":"Forest near Emond's Field","description":"A place where Rand finds himself after fleeing the village that was captured by Trollocs."},{"name":"House of Tam al'Thor","description":"The home where Rand and Tam live, now left in ruins after being attacked by Trollocs."},{"name":"Barn of Tam al'Thor","description":"The barn where Rand seeks supplies but finds it in shambles with animals and carts gone."},{"name":"Near Emond's Field forest","description":"A forested area outside of Emond's Field where Rand and Tam are traveling through heavily laden with fear and fatigue."},{"name":"Westwood","description":"A part of Emond's Field where the fires from the Bel Tine festival were burned, causing a stench due to the destruction and presence of dead Trollocs."},{"name":"Home of Mistress al'Vere","description":"A place in Emond's Field where Rand and his unconscious father, Tam, are cared for."}],"summary":"In Emond's Field, after Trol